<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900417-0037</DOCNO><DOCID>900417-0037.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- National Business Systems Inc.:   Holders Clear New Name,   Plan for Recapitalization</HL><DATE>04/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15</SO><CO>   T.HIL T.NBS</CO><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)</IN><LP>   National Business Systems Inc. said shareholders approveda recapitalization plan that includes changing the Torontocompany's name to Consolidated NBS Inc.   The plan also calls for consolidating the outstandingcommon shares on a 1-for-10 basis and creating three newclasses of preferred shares. It didn't give the value of thenew preferred issues.</LP><TEXT>   At last report, National Business had about 16 millionshares outstanding.   The company said its noteholders will exchange 20 millionCanadian dollars ($17.2 million) of senior subordinated notesfor an equivalent amount of debentures convertible into ClassAAA cumulative participating preferred shares.   The company also plans a rights offering which would allowshareholders to purchase an additional C$20 million of theconvertible debentures.   Hees International Bancorp Inc., which was retained in1987 to manage and turn around the troubled credit-cardaccessory manufacturing concern, said it will take anyconvertible debentures not subscribed for under the offering.</TEXT></DOC>